<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 07 at 8:30PM MDT  by NWS Billings</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Sweet
Grass County through 900 PM MDT...
At 830 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Big Timber, moving northwest at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail and heavy rain.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern Sweet
Grass County.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
